# Keep build context slim + prevent host artifacts from clobbering
# the freshly-installed /app/node_modules inside the frontend image.
#
# ── Why each entry ──
# node_modules/.next/.pnpm-store : COPY . . in Dockerfile.frontend line 14
#   overwrites /app/node_modules just installed at line 11 → "cannot copy
#   to non-directory" on buildkit cachemounts. Discovered live during L9
#   quick-start.sh end-to-end testing on 2026-04-17.
# __pycache__/.pytest_cache : Python bytecode + test caches bloat context.
# .git : ~GB of pack files not needed at build time.
# data/*.db : local dev SQLite files shouldn't leak into image.
# test-results/playwright-report : test run output, not shipped.
# .venv : backend tests sometimes create a local venv.
# .agent_workspaces : dev workspace clones can be huge.
#
# ── Pattern semantics (L10 #337 image-size fix) ──
# Docker's .dockerignore matches patterns relative to the build context
# root. A bare `.venv` only matches `./.venv`, NOT `./backend/.venv` —
# nested dirs need `**/.venv`. Before the fix, `backend/.venv` (168 MB
# of duplicate site-packages) leaked into the backend image, pushing
# it to 1.34 GB. Use `**/<pattern>` for anything that can appear at
# any depth.

# Frontend
node_modules
**/node_modules
.next
**/.next
.pnpm-store
**/.pnpm-store
.turbo
**/.turbo
.eslintcache
**/.eslintcache

# Python
__pycache__
**/__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache
**/.pytest_cache
.mypy_cache
**/.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache
**/.ruff_cache
*.egg-info
**/*.egg-info
.venv
**/.venv

# Local data / runtime state
data/*.db
data/*.db-journal
data/*.db-wal
data/*.db-shm
data/.bootstrap_state.json
.artifacts
.sdks
.agent_workspaces

# Tests / CI artifacts
test-results
playwright-report
coverage
htmlcov
.tox
.nyc_output

# VCS / editor
.git
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
*.swp

# Env secrets (the real .env is mounted via env_file in compose, not COPYed)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.pem
*.key

# Dockerignore itself
.dockerignore
